Imperial Holdings Ltd. (IPL) , the South
African transport company which on July 11 said itâ€™s in talks to
make an acquisition outside its home market, declined the most
in more than five months.  The stock fell as much as 5.3 percent, the biggest intraday
drop since Jan. 31, to 117.50 rand and was trading at 117.65
rand as of 3 p.m. in Johannesburg. Almost 667,000 shares were
traded compared to the daily average over the past six months of
